      "title": "Rio de Janeiro's \"homegrown\" LLM appears to be a merge of an existing model",
      "url": "https://github.com/nex-agi/Nex-N2/issues/4",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48528371",
      "score": 182,
      "comments": 104,
      "author": "unrvl22",
      "published": "2026-06-14T15:37:31Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Technical analysis suggests Rio's municipal LLM is a merge of existing open-weights models rather than a custom pre-trained system.",
        "Model merging via tools like mergekit enables rapid, low-cost LLM creation, but risks deceptive sovereign AI branding by public entities.",
        "Practitioners should use lineage tracking, license compliance audits, and evaluation benchmarks to verify claims of novel, custom-built AI models."
      ]
    },
    {
